---

<section class="section" id="projects">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="kicker reveal"><span class="num">02</span><span class="lbl">Projects</span><span class="rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2 reveal">Things I <span class="g-pink">build</span> after hours</h2>
    <p class="lead reveal d1" style="margin-bottom:34px;">Mostly MCP servers that teach Claude new tricks — plus the occasional bit of hardware.</p>
    <div class="cards cols-2">
      <article class="card reveal d1" style="--accent: var(--cyan);">
        <svg class="emblem" viewBox="0 0 48 48" fill="none" stroke-width="2.4" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
          <rect x="7" y="12" width="34" height="24" rx="3"></rect>
          <polyline points="8 14 24 27 40 14"></polyline>
        </svg>
        <h3>mailbox-mcp-server</h3>
        <p>Connects Claude to mailbox.org — search and read mail, manage calendar events and Sieve filters over IMAP, SMTP and CalDAV.</p>
        <div class="meta"><span>TypeScript</span><span>MCP</span><span>IMAP · CalDAV</span></div>
        <a class="link-ext" href="https://github.com/soenkenils/mailbox-mcp-server" target="_blank" rel="noopener">View on GitHub ↗</a>
      </article>
      <article class="card reveal d2" style="--accent: var(--pink);">
        <svg class="emblem" viewBox="0 0 48 48" fill="none" stroke-width="2.4" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
          <rect x="8" y="11" width="32" height="28" rx="3"></rect>
          <line x1="8" y1="19" x2="40" y2="19"></line>
          <line x1="17" y1="7" x2="17" y2="14"></line>
          <line x1="31" y1="7" x2="31" y2="14"></line>
          <circle cx="24" cy="29" r="4"></circle>
        </svg>
        <h3>soverin-mcp</h3>
        <p>The same idea for soverin.net: email and calendar as MCP tools, with connection pooling and a circuit breaker under the hood.</p>
        <div class="meta"><span>TypeScript</span><span>MCP</span><span>SMTP</span></div>
        <a class="link-ext" href="https://github.com/soenkenils/soverin-mcp" target="_blank" rel="noopener">View on GitHub ↗</a>
      </article>
      <article class="card reveal d2" style="--accent: var(--purple);">
        <svg class="emblem" viewBox="0 0 48 48" fill="none" stroke-width="2.4" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
          <circle cx="15" cy="33" r="5"></circle>
          <circle cx="35" cy="29" r="5"></circle>
          <line x1="20" y1="33" x2="20" y2="13"></line>
          <line x1="40" y1="29" x2="40" y2="9"></line>
          <line x1="20" y1="13" x2="40" y2="9"></line>
        </svg>
        <h3>playlists-tidal-mcp</h3>
        <p>An MCP server for TIDAL — playlist management, catalog search and smart playlists sequenced on radio-programming principles.</p>
        <div class="meta"><span>TypeScript</span><span>OAuth PKCE</span><span>TIDAL API</span></div>
      </article>
      <article class="card reveal d3" style="--accent: var(--orange);">
        <svg class="emblem" viewBox="0 0 48 48" fill="none" stroke-width="2.4" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
          <rect x="16" y="14" width="16" height="27" rx="3"></rect>
          <line x1="21" y1="7" x2="21" y2="14"></line>
          <rect x="20" y="20" width="8" height="6" rx="1"></rect>
          <line x1="21" y1="32" x2="27" y2="32"></line>
          <line x1="21" y1="36" x2="27" y2="36"></line>
        </svg>
        <h3>walkie-talkie</h3>
        <p>A pair of ESP32 walkie-talkies on M5Stick hardware, built for my kids — soldering, C++ and two very happy field testers.</p>
        <div class="meta"><span>C++</span><span>ESP32</span><span>M5Stick</span></div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
